Hospitalized after vaccination with acute submassive PE.  ASSESSMENT / PLAN: Patient is a 53-year-old male in no significant past medical history who presented with complaints of progressively worsening shortness of breath, chest pressure and was found to have acute submassive pulmonary embolism for which he underwent successful mechanical thrombectomy per Interventional Radiology.  Subsequent bilateral lower extremity DVT ultrasound demonstrated acute DVTs in the left popliteal, posterior tibial, peroneal veins. DETAILS OF HOSPITAL STAY: PRESENTING PROBLEM: Acute pulmonary embolism, unspecified pulmonary embolism type, unspecified whether acute cor pulmonale present (HCC) [I26.99] HOSPITAL COURSE: The patient is a 53-year-old male in no significant past medical history who is admitted for Acute Saddle Pulmonary Embolism. In the ED, the patient was tachycardic, tachypenic requiring 2 L of O2. CT angiogram thorax showed saddle embolus with extensive bilateral pulmonary emboli and evidence for right heart failure. He was immediately started on IV Heparin. PERT Team was activated and the patient underwent a successful mechanical thrombectomy with IR. Dopplers of the lower extremity showed Left lower popliteal, posterior tibial and peroneal DVTs. After 24 hours of hemodynamically stable vitals, the patient was transition to Eliquis.  The patient stay was complicated with elevated blood glucose along with Hba1c of 9.7. Endocrinology was consulted and started the patient with Lantus and LDC. The patient will be discharged with diabetic regimen and followed up with PCP/outpatient Endocrine.    The patient was stable, AOx4, without complications and discharged safely to his home with his wife.

Patient had a reaction immediately after the JJ vaccine. Patient passed out for 10-15seconds, her body stiffened up, she felt hot and then cold and started sweating excessively. Patients eyes closed briefly and then opened. Patient then became conscious and was unware what had happened.  Patient is not on any medication and had not eaten all morning. After administering the vaccine a small amount of blood came out. I gave her a cotton ball to apply on the area and to hold. After 20-30 seconds she said she felt faint and hot all of a sudden. Her body then went limp and her eyes began to close. Her body then stiffened up for a few seconds. After shouting her name a few times she regained consciousness and was able to talk. she didn't realize what had happened. Her body was fine again but she had urinated during the episode.  Upon speaking to the patient I learnt that she was nervous about the vaccination and she had felt dizzy in the past when giving blood. I observed the patient over the next 45 minutes. Her speech was fine, she was still a little light headed. She was in her seat for 40 minutes, then I asked her to stand and to move a little to see how she was. She was able to walk a bit but then sat down as she still felt light headed. She than sipped on water and continued talking and seemed to get some energy back.

Over the next 48 hours the rash darkened and spread to the entire body causing pain in her skin. The myalgia became nearly unbearable and both Ibuprofen and Acetaminophen didn't put a dent in the pain. One side of her face swelled so that one eye could only partially open. The nausea and stomach pain worsened so that she couldn't eat. Headache became intense. By 48 hours post vaccine she became delirious - her speech was slurred and difficult to comprehend. She would fall asleep for a few minutes and wake up unaware of where she was or what was happening. She never got a fever but did have chills. Around this time I called a relative who is a doctor to seek advice and Diphenhydramine was recommended. Benedryl helped immensely. 30 minutes after taking it she could speak clearly, was more alert, pain became tolerable, and her appetite returned. Symptoms and swelling returned when the Benedryl wore off so she continued taking it every 4 hours for the next two days until it wasn't necessary any more. The myalgia, stomach pain and headache persisted for 7 days. At 8 days post vaccine (today) a mild headache, mild and intermittent stomach pain, and mild fatigue are her only remaining symptoms. Again, went to the doctor and was told i had no UTI. The next day it was unbearable....the pain and uncomfortableness, so i went to the ER.  They ran tests and everything looked clear. Went home and suffered with this pain, bloat, constipation, pressure to pee. Throughout the past month i have seen a GI doctor, Urologist, and gynecologist. Everything looks clear and good and no one has any idea what has happened to me. I was perfectly healthy before the immunization. I believe the immunization inflamed my GI system, and Bladder. Slowly things are returning to normal but I know this had to have been caused by something.

Adverse event: PT here for first dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine. PT reported feeling anxiety before vaccination, but indicated that she was ready for her vaccination. Immediately post-vaccination, PT experienced an apparent vasovagal response, presenting with palor, slumped posture. PT's eyes were open, but PT was unresponsive and later reported no memory of events. PT became responsive within 2 minutes, but remained "shakey" and pale. RN was in attendance and provided initial assessment/response. RN also responded to PT. Aid was called at 1251 and EMTs arrived at 1253. Aid assessed PT, took vital signs (1256: BP 104/56 laying, HR 70, SPO2 98% on room air, 1303 BP 110/62 laying, HR 87, SPO2 99% RA, 1307: BP 96/58 sitting, SPO2 99%RA, 1311: BP 106/62 sitting, SPO2 99% RA).  Treatment: PT was assisted to lay down on cot, water and juice were provided and consumed, cool compress were provided. Psychosocial support provided. Education to PT and mother to monitor for further s/s and to seek out urgent care if more were noted.  Outcome: PT's color improved soon after laying down, PT reported "feeling better" after consuming juice and water. PT sat at edge of cot without difficulty, walked down hallway without difficulty. PT medically cleared by EMS at 1223, exited facility with mother in private vehicle.
OTHER_MEDS: Mother reports dtr takes "ADHD medications" but cannot name the medication.

I administered patient's second Moderna vaccine and after about 5 minutes in my vaccine observation area she stated that she felt dizzy. She did feel dizzy after the first shot as well but at the time she was fasting for religious reasons and her dizzy spell resolved after she broke her fast and drank orange soda. The patient was concerned that would happen again and I made sure that she had eaten today.   Her breathing became rapid and she was sweaty. I gave her a wet washcloth to put on her head and neck. I monitored her vital signs and encouraged her to try to take deep breaths and put her head in between her knees. After a little while she said she was cold and was shivering I gave her her jacket. She asked my staff to call 9-1-1 and was panicked.   I kept encouraging her to try to take deep breaths and slow down her breathing including meditation techniques and breathing techniques as I thought it was a panic attack as she had no other signs of allergic reaction. No hives no difficulty breathing other than rapid rate.  The paramedics came and surmised the same that the patient was having a panic attack and asked if she wanted to be transported to the hospital in which she responded "yes". She was then taken in the ambulance to the hospital.
CUR_ILL: none, after first dose of Moderna was dizzy but at the time the patient was fasting for religious reasons. Patient was given a sugary drink and quickly recovered.

72 yo F presented for second dose of Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine.  She had no issues with previous dose. She was on her normal medications and used a single dose of her rescue albuterol inhaler with in 15 minutes of receiving her vaccine.  Immediately following the administration of the vaccine, she began to feels lightheaded. She also felt flushed and her heart was racing.  She started to have feelings of anxiety as well. She was placed in a 5 deg head low position.  On initial exam, her speech was slow and difficult to hear.  She was coherent and able to answer questions and give sxs.  On initial exam she was pale.  Non-labored breathing.  He had a irregularly irregular pulse with a mild tachycardia with a rate in the 110's. She was hemodynamically stable with a BP in the 150's/90's. At this point EMS was called to transfer her to a location which could better assess her.  further history was obtained from the patient including the recent dose of albuterol PMHx of CHF w a-fib and  COPD  She was moved to the procedure room via wheel chair and placed on pulse ox monitoring while leads were placed for an ECG. Her initial pulse ox was 93% and she was placed on O2 at 3l via NC.  Her f/u BP was 120's/70's.  EMS arrived, report was given and she was transferred to their care for transport to ED.

Drove home, had severe diarrhea , chills, fever. My arm swelled up and hurt. My lower back was in severe pain. My upper right back thigh - between the buttocks and knee had a horrible pain in it. Very severe pain and it started radiating down my calf muscle and then to the front of shin. Stayed for days on the back of my thigh in my right leg. I continued having very severe vertigo. I would have to run and throw up if I tried to move or go back to bed. The nausea never went away. That was lasted for 8 days. I went to my doctor's office - I drove to the office - they moved all the doctor's across town for Sutter and I couldn't make it before they closed and I had to go home. I couldn't make it. Just driving there was impossible - It was really bad. Didn't have  a doctor visit at all then. The dr. prescribed a medication for vertigo. The pharmacist said to buy the OTC medication for vertigo so I bought it but it didn't help. That made me doped up and sleepy but still nauseated. I got a spike behind my ear on the right hand side of head - in that little pocket - headaches would come there.  I still have weird vertigo and dizziness - intermittently- although I always have a dull nauseous feeling. Every now and then I have to run and throw up - it's like my body is tired of feeling dizzy. (Information gained secondhand from patient's close friend as patient was intubated and sedated at the time that potential relationship between events and vaccine administration recognized). 77 yo F with no known significant PMH (was independent in ADLs, active, line-danced twice/week) who developed nausea, headache, fatigue on first day after first dose of Moderna vaccine. Friend reports that patient complained of "just not feeling right" following vaccine administration. Complained of poor sleep, poor appetite, dyspepsia and began complaining of lower extremity swelling in the weeks following vaccine administration. Was no longer able to line-dance, etc. Was fatigued. Her friends became concerned and encouraged her to seek medical attention, patient reported that she had was prescribed "water pill" and told to "lay off salt,". Friends later found out that she had lied about doctor's visit and was self-medicating with over the counter  "water pills" for all of the water weight she was gaining. Eventually developed worsening shortness of breath. Admitted to hospital on 5/4 with shortness of breath and worsening abdominal pain. Found to have systolic heart failure (EF 20-30%) and was in SVT. Also diagnosed with UTI and SMV thrombus. Grossly anasarcic on exam. Treated for heart failure with diuretic and for her UTI with antibiotics, was started on Heparin drip for SMV thrombus. Underwent left heart catheterization at OSH that was negative for significant CAD. Developed worsening septic shock and was transferred to our hospital for higher level of care. Unfortunately had ongoing decline, found to be fungemic. Eventually succumbed to her septic shock, passed away on 5/14/21.  Patient had second dose of vaccine on 3/18/21 according to vaccine card in her purse. Friend states that because of symptoms she developed after first dose of vaccine, she was fearful of getting second dose.  Friends insist that she was well before the vaccine---knee pain was limiting factor for her activity level, never shortness of breath. Of note, several friends tested positive for COVID on 2/11/21, the week prior to patient receiving her vaccine. Patient tested negative and reportedly got tested at frequent intervals and was always negative.

Kaleidoscope vision  twice, followed by 5-10 minutes of severe confusion and inability to remember words and son's date of birth.  The fogginess with feelings of a headache coming on for about an hour afterwards.  I was working out (as I do 3 times a week with weight training) when the kaleidoscope vision came on, but I didn't initially feel any other effects and since it went away within 5-10 minutes, I continued with my workout.  When I was driving home, it returned and the episode of confusion occurred as soon as I reached my home.  I went to the ER after looking up symptoms following the confusion and decided to get checked out since a mini-stroke seemed possible.  I have no history of migraines or other health conditions.  At the ER, they ran some bloodwork, but I have not received the results of those tests.  They also performed a CT scan and said that looked clear, but I have not seen any official results for that either.  I have also been advised by a physician that a CT scan won't show signs of a stroke and that I should have received an MRI.  I will be following up with a PCP to request an MRI and will provide those results when I have them.  I have had one other episode of the Kaleidoscope vision since the original event, and I was sitting down watching a movie at the time.  It went away within the same 5-10 minutes and I had what felt like a mild headache coming on, but no other symptoms.  And I have never had any migraines or regular headaches/vision events such as these before.

I have an appointment scheduled with my physician to discuss these symptoms. In the mean time I self treated at home with relaxation techniques, sleep and time.

Patient called out reporting that he had fainted/blacked out while sitting in chair across from the pharmacy counter. The patient was sitting with legs were stretched out and his head was laying back on a shelf that was immediately behind the chair he was in.  I immediately went out to converse with the patient. I called for someone to bring him a cool drink and gave him a cool compress for his forehead. He pulled his mask down below is nose to breathe more freely. While he was drinking the pineapple drink I asked if this had ever happened before while receiving a vaccine or during a blood draw. He said never as an adult but as a child he did have fainting spells. When asked if he had eaten at all during the morning or afternoon he reported he had not but had only drank water and coffee. After about 10-15 minutes he started to feel better. I asked if I could call someone to drive him home, he said he was fine and when he went to get up to go he reported that his arms were tingling. I asked his permission to call 911 so he could be evaluated in the ER. He agreed. 911 was dispatched. Paramedics took his blood pressure and found his diastolic pressure to be 100. He was asked if he had been diagnosed with HTN or if he was taking any medications to treat it. He denied. They suggested that he be taken to the ER to which he declined to go. The paramedics escorted him out of the store at approximately 2:15pm.

On 4/1/2021 Patient had at least one seizure at home and upon arriving at the ER/hospital had a severe seizure.  She was admitted to the hospital for treatment and was in the intensive care unit for about 9 days.  She was given seizure medicine along with other fluids to keep her hydrated and fed.  Multiple EEGs were taken to track the electrical activity within her brain - which even with high doses of medication was very active.  A spinal tap was done to test for infection and no viruses were found.  An MRI was completed to identify what part of the brain was being impacted.   The area of the brain that was impacted was the side and the images showed it was very inflamed.  She has since been moved to a physical therapy facility to try to help her improve.  At this time, she still needs assistance for all activities and would not be able to return home due to the level of care she needs.  Her current diagnosis is autoimmune encephalitis.  She has never had seizures before and this one began about two weeks after receiving her first dose of the COVID-19 shot.  She has been unable to receive her second shot due to being in the hospital and physical therapy facility.  Due to the timing of the seizure event, we are very concerned with her receiving her second shot as well.
LAB_DATA: MRI, EEGs (every day during her hospital stay), spinal tap
OTHER_MEDS: Metoprolol succinate ER, Hydralazinie HCI, Losartan potassium, Omeprazole Dr, Folbic, Seroquel
HISTORY: Kidney disease, high blood pressure, diabetes, alzheimers

On 5.13.21, the closing pharmacist,  and the closing technician, filed a salvage claim of 2mls of unused Moderna Covid Vaccine (4 immunizations) that had not been used during the day. The product was salvaged under the Senior technician, as he had visually instructed both of them how to correctly salvage unused vaccine before he left his shift at 6:30 pm. Once salvaged, neither employee correctly placed the vial in the hazardous waste bin and left in on the counter in the vaccine area of the pharmacy.  On the morning of 5.14.21, the opening pharmacist, and opening technicians, saw the unused vaccine vial from the previous evening 5.13.21, and did not correctly dispose of the vial nor quarantine the vial. They explained they did not know where to dispose of it and was waiting on senior tech to arrive for his shift for further direction.  At 10am, when the first patient arrived for a vaccine, tech checked in the patient and gave patient the VAR. While patient was filling out VAR, tech removed one Moderna vial from the refrigerator so the vaccine could come to room temperature for the appropriate amount of time. She popped the plastic vial lid off of the vial and cleaned the rubber stopper with alcohol. Once the patient was through filling out the VAR, technician  took over the transaction and headed to the vaccine area. Technician saw that 2 vials were present, unknowing that one vial was expired and quaratined, and added a tik mark to the Moderna Beyond Use Time label thinking 6 shots had already been given earlier in the day and drew up the syringe on current and 2 additional patients from the expired vial. This is verified by the tik marks added to the Beyond Use Label by tech in a different colored ink pen. At a point after these three said immunizations were given, senior tech saw that there was 2 vials on the counter realizing that one vial was from the day before and correctly disposed of the vial.  Later in the day, senior tech told everyone to remember to put tick marks on the vials they use and tech said she had placed her tiks on the 1st vial Beyond Use Label. Senior tech said there was no vial from earlier and asked if she has used the expired vial before he got there. Tech said she drew up at least 3 shots from the unknowingly expired vial.  Upon learning this information, senior tech looked for the on duty pharmacist,  as she heard the same information that was just presented. Pharmacist asked senior tech to go ahead and reach out to the pharmacy manager,  to make sure we correctly document this in system. Pharmacist then reached out to store manager,  to go over the correct standard operation procedures of this said event.  Pharmacist first contacted store Liability Intake Process to report the immunization event. The responding agent took the information that they needed and gave us reference report number. The pharmacy is to call back once we know the names and date of births of the corresponding patients who were involved. Next, pharmacist called the Moderna manufacture to report the event and to ask for information on potential side effects for the patients involved. Again, the responding agents gathered all the information they needed and escalated the information to their Medical Affairs team who will reach back out to us shortly. They advised pharmacist that this event is to be reported to the  reporting system.  The pharmacy vaccine area is in a blind spot for security cameras but by deductive reasoning it was determined by pharmacy team the 3 patients who received the expired vaccine. After the correct patients were identified, pharmacist reached out to the patients and was unable to speak to any of them but left voicemails asking them to call back 5.15.21 after 9 am and speak directly to the pharmacist due to an urgent matter.  Lastly, pharmacist then submitted the according reports to both the adverse reporting systems.

The product was salvaged under the Senior technician, J, as he had visually instructed both of them how to correctly salvage unused vaccine before he left his shift at 6:30 pm. Once salvaged, neither employee correctly placed the vial in the hazardous waste bin and left in on the counter in the vaccine area of the pharmacy.  On the morning of 5.14.21, the opening pharmacist, M, and opening technicians, C and C, saw the unused vaccine vial from the previous evening 5.13.21, and did not correctly dispose of the vial nor quaratine the vial. They explained they did not know where to dispose of it and was waiting on J to arrive for his shift for further direction.  At 10am, when the first patient arrived for a vaccine, C checked in the patient and gave patient the VAR. While patient was filling out VAR, C removed one Moderna vial from the refrigerator so the vaccine could come to room temperature for the appropriate amount of time. She popped the plastic vial lid off of the vial and cleaned the rubber stopper with alcohol. Once the patient was through filling out the VAR, technician T took over the transaction and headed to the vaccine area. T saw that 2 vials were present, unknowing that one vial was expired and quaratined, and added a tik mark to the Moderna Beyond Use Time label thinking 6 shots had already been given earlier in the day and drew up the syringe on current and 2 additional patients from the expired vial. This is verified by the tik marks added to the Beyond Use Label by T in a different colored ink pen. At a point after these three said immunizations were given , J saw that there was 2 vials on the counter realizing that one vial was from the day before and correctly disposed of the vial.  Later in the day, J told everyone to remember to put tick marks on the vials they use and T said she had placed her tiks on the 1st vial Beyond Use Label. J said there was no vial from earlier and asked if she has used the expired vial before he got there. T said she drew up at least 3 shots from the unknowingly expired vial.  Upon learning this information, J looked for the on duty pharmacist, C, as she heard the same information that was just presented. C asked J to go ahead and reach out to the pharmacy manager, B, to make sure we correctly document this in VAERS and STARS. C then reached out to store manager, C, to go over the correct standard operation procedures of this said event.  C first contacted Pharmacy Liability Intake Process to report the immunization event. The responding agent took the information that they needed and gave us reference #14627835. The pharmacy is to call back once we know the names and date of births of the corresponding patients who were involved. Next, C called the Moderna manufacture to report the event and to ask for information on potential side effects for the patients involved. I got the vaccine and the following morning I had the worst headache I have ever had. I felt like my head was going to explode, and I took ibuprofen and Tylenol. I also had a fever and excruciating pain at the injection site, this all went away within 3 days. On 05/07/2021 I woke up with a really bad headache and I was dizzy, I took ibuprofen and Tylenol and it seemed to be getting better. And finally on 05/11/2021 I woke up again with a headache and dizziness, this is the day I went to my primary care doctor and he told me that he has seen this pretty frequently with the moderna vaccine. He said that it was brain swelling and inflammation. He told me to take ibuprofen and Tylenol every 6 hours for a week and that if I was still experiencing these side effects then I can come back and he will prescribe me steroids. It has now been 3 days, and my head still hurts and doesn?t feel normal. He also told me that if I get tingling in my fingers or blurred vision to go to an emergency room right away.

This writer was drawing up 2 doses of Pfizer for this patient and their sibling. For one of these patients, I had to open a new Pfizer vial, but accidentally drew up the whole vial without reconstituting with 1.8 mL of water. As a result, one of the two siblings received a dose that was supposed to be worth 6 doses of the Pfizer vaccine. I contacted the patients' father 15 minutes later, who stated that the patients were doing okay and reported no symptoms. I also reported this incident to a district manager. Per my manager, I informed the patients' father about what happened, asked him to monitor his children for symptoms, and report to the ED if the experience anything severe. I also told them that this dose would not be valid and they would have to return to the pharmacy to have their 1st dose dose again. He understood and accepted this information. Bottom line, there was no actual symptoms reported, but I am concerned about the higher dose either of these kids (12 year-old female & 15 year-old male) may have received and pray they will be okay.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The first day, I had slight arm soreness with nothing more. When I woke up on day two, I noticed my arm had swelled more than usual (basing off my previous dose in my right arm) and was extremely hot, tender, and had two circular red patches. That night, the redness and swelling had spread into a medium sized circle, and began to itch and still be very hot upon touch. Upon looking later that night, at approximately 11pm EST, the swelling and redness had gotten larger.  On day three, the redness only got worse, and is slowly spread more over the area, with intense itching, but no longer is as sore as it was the day prior. I have iced the area, moved my arm around more to help the swelling go down, taken a hot shower, and about 600mg of Ibuprofen each day since the second dose. On 5/13/2021 patient developed a cough in the evening. Patient woke up not feeling well on 5/14/2021, and also had nausea and vomiting. Patient was driving a vehicle when he had a seizure. No prior history of seizures. Drifted off the road, no significant damage to vehicle. Patient post-ictal following seizure, seizure activity was witnessed by bystanders. CT brain showed small subdural hematoma. A CTA chest performed due to hypoxemia and tachycardia at Hospital  showed Multifocal groundglass type nodular infiltrates throughout the right lung involving the upper lobe, middle lobe, and lower lobe, minimal left lower lobe patchy infiltrate, as well as patient's known thymoma. These multifocal groundglass infiltrates were not previously mentioned on a CT chest performed on 4/10/2021.  Patient was transferred to this facility for evaluation by neurosurgery. Patient was mildly tachycardic, hypoxemic to 88% on room air, and tachypneic. Patient reported decreased sense of taste & smell for 1 month, which he attributed to his losartan use.  A covid/flu/rsv PCR on 4/10/2021 was negative, and a viral respiratory pathogen panel with covid PCR was negative on 5/14/2021, as was an antigen & NAAT for COVID on 5/14/2021.  Patient was treated with antibiotics and admitted for further management.
LAB_DATA: CT Brain (repeat on 5/14): Mild asymmetric hyperdense thickening of the posterior falx measuring approximately 4 mm compatible with known subdural hematoma.   CTA Chest (5/14): Multifocal groundglass type nodular infiltrates throughout the right lung involving the upper lobe, middle lobe, and lower lobe, minimal left lower lobe patchy infiltrate; known thymoma present  CT Chest w/ contrast (4/10/2021): Subsegmental opacities involving the left lung likely representing atelectasis. Additional nodular and patchy opacities which may represent infectious or inflammatory process and less likely malignancy. Heterogeneous large anterior mediastinal mass which is partially calcified measuring approximately 90 x 136 mm with mass effect on the aortic arch and extending to the anterior chest wall. There is mass effect on the left pulmonary artery which is likely encased. Additionally, there is mass effect on the left mainstem and upper lobe bronchus. The anterior left upper lobe is partially collapsed. Additional left lower lobe subsegmental opacities likely representing atelectasis.  MRI Brain 5/15: Pending Viral Resp Panel + COVID 5/14: Negative CBC w/ WBC 25.4; 88% neutrophils; plt 245 CRP 3.5 Potassium 2.7

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt developed sharp chest pain, intermittent, positional, severe at times.  Occurred within 24 hours of 2nd vaccine administration.  Seemed to improve with ibuprofen taken. LAB_DATA: Troponin I = 1.5 Echocardiogram:  preserved EF 60-65%, no pericardial effusion

Muscle spasms in his upper torso / involuntary muscles spasms / still having them; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of muscle spasm in a 16-year-old male patient who received Men B NVS (Bexsero) for prophylaxis.   Co-suspect products included meningococcal B recom vaccine + aloh + omv pre-filled syringe device (Bexsero Pre-Filled Syringe Device) injection syringe for prophylaxis and Men ACWY-CRM NVS (Menveo) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included MCV4 vaccine with an associated reaction of no adverse event (received dose 1 on unknown date with no problems).   On 7th May 2021 15:30, the patient received the 1st dose of Bexsero (intramuscular). On 7th May 2021, the patient started Bexsero Pre-Filled Syringe Device. On 7th May 2021 15:30, the patient received Menveo (intramuscular). On 7th May 2021 18:30, 3 hrs after receiving Bexsero, Bexsero Pre-Filled Syringe Device and Menveo, the patient experienced muscle spasm. On an unknown date, the outcome of the muscle spasm was not recovered/not resolved.   The reporter considered the muscle spasm to be related to Bexsero and Bexsero Pre-Filled Syringe Device. It was unknown if the reporter considered the muscle spasm to be related to Menveo. This report is made by GSK without prejudice and does not imply any admission or liability for the incident or its consequences.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by the mother of the patient. The reporter claimed that her son had no health issues and was perfectly healthy before receiving  the Menveo booster shot for college. This was his last meningitis vaccine for college. The patient got Bexsero and Menveo both in the left arm. The reporter said about 3 hours after the shot the patient started having the involuntary muscle spasms, it affected his upper torso. The reporter said if he was standing up he was fine but if he sat or lounged or laid down he was prone to it, spasms looked like he was having a seizure. The patient could talk through it, no cognitive loss, appetite was fine. The reporter said they had been to the pediatrician and to the emergency room regarding this. On the day of reporting they had an EEG test done at the neurologist and they had not received the results. She offered to send a video of what it looked like. The patient's condition till the time of reporting remained unchanged. The reporter said that the physician's did not think that the MCV-4 (Meningococcal ACWY) vaccine was the one which was causing the muscle spasms since he had already had dose 1 before with no issues. The reporter was asked if she had the lot number/expiration date of the Bexsero she said no. It was the Bexsero that the reporter believed was causing the muscle spasms. Note: The reporter did not have the trade name of MCV-4 (Meningococcal ACWY) but she thought it might have been made by Pfizer, therefore it might have been GSK's product Menveo.
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 20210511; Test Name: EEG; Result Unstructured Data: (Test Result:No result,Unit:unknown,Normal Low:,Normal High:) not received results yet

Patient believed that she was having a side effect from dose number one. She has had a persistent pain in her neck/upper back area from the morning after she got the vaccine. She never had neck pain before, so she had been watching it. She said it hurt pretty bad and it's gotten worse. It was moderate to severe. She was waiting for her doctor to call her back. Patient mentioned that in the information she was given, this side effect wasn't stated so she was wondering if it was normal or what she should do. Patient also reported that she had read a bunch of threads online about people reporting neck pain after the Pfizer vaccine and some had mentioned lymph node swelling. The patient also reported that on 07Apr2021, with her first COVID 19 vaccine she had this muscle pain on her shoulder, back and neck area on the side where she got the COVID 19 vaccine. It began like a day after she received the COVID 19 vaccine. The pain kept getting worse and by day 7 or 8, after the vaccine, the pain was really bad, and she couldn't lift her head up when she would wake up in the morning. She tried to contact her primary care doctor but didn't hear back from that office. Her muscle pain finally started to go away. She spoke to someone at Pfizer  about 2 weeks ago who was going over statistics with her from the clinical study that was done. The patient was told that 21 percent of people experienced new or worsened muscle pain. Nothing else had changed in any other area of her life or any other activity. The only outlier was the COVID 19 vaccine. That's why she called because it was severe pain. She wanted to go to the emergency department but what was waiting to hear back from her primary care doctor, but that office never got back to her. It was scary, she couldn't lift her head for a few days, and she took Ibuprofen. Now her second COVID 19 vaccine was scheduled in 2 days on 05May2021. She felt very hesitant about getting the second vaccine. She lived alone and she didn't want to go through her muscle pain again. She didn't want her family to have to drive to her house to help her. She was following up with Pfizer to see if there was any guidance on whether someone with her experience should receive her second COVID 19 vaccine. She reported that she called her doctor 2 to 3 times daily for 3 days and never spoke to anyone from that office. By then the weekend was there. On the third day of trying to call her doctor, she left her doctor a crazy voicemail because it was not right that no one was returning her calls and her doctor was unavailable to her. At the time she had a change of work status, so she didn't have health insurance. She had health insurance now and had not seen a new doctor. Her muscle pain was still lingering. She was been trying to do neck exercises and stretches. She was never had pain in that area before. The patient spoke to a girl who worked at the urgent care. This girl who answered the phone at the urgent care told the patient that the same thing happened to her, it was all neck pain. At that point, the patient was aware that what she experienced had happened to someone else. The patient was trying to confirm if her neck pain was related to the vaccine or not but the girl who answered the phone at the urgent care, didn't really say anything else. There was not a product complaint to report. There was a medical information request. Further probing could not be done as consumer hung up the call abruptly. Hence, limited information was available over the call. The outcome of the events was unknown.  No follow-up attempts are needed. No further information is expected. And it went on for 10 days every other day. Now it just happened. I just unloaded yesterday (29Apr2021). It all just started happening after the 2nd vaccine. It may be related or may not. The urologist said that's strange and they said there's nothing they can do about it. I will be seeing the neurologist on 07Jun2021." Caller calling about the Pfizer COVID vaccine. She states that 2 days after getting the second shot every now and then her mind would go off, like a mini seizure and then she would loose her urine. She states that she has never had this issue before. It has been going on for almost over a month now, but it has been going down a little less, but it's still happening. She is going to a neurologist, but the neurologist can't see her until June. She is wondering has anyone else had an issue with this? She states she has been to a urologist, but they say they can't do anything for her and that she needs to see a neurologist. She states that it is very strange. She does state that it is becoming less and less, and it is like every 4 days now. She states she did have a 6 day stretch where she didn't have any incidence of the mini seizure or loosing her urine. She states she has never had anything happen to her like this, not even close. It happens out of the blue, and she doesn't even feel the sensation to urinate. She states she could be talking to someone, or in a store talking to someone and her mind goes out for just a second and then she just pees. She states that she is aware of what is going on. Caller states that she doesn't know what a mini seizure is like and does not know how to describe this event. However, it is usually when she is talking to someone, her mind might go off for a second then she just pees. She states it's weird. She states that it is usually when she is out, and that it doesn't happen at home. She states that she doesn't have the sensation of having to go to the bathroom she just goes. She says it's weird, nothing like this has ever happened before. She doesn't have a problem with fizzing out for a couple seconds. Caller states she doesn't want to use mini-seizure because then that marks her of having epilepsy. She also states that her doctor told her not to describe it as a seizure because they are not sure what it is yet. She wants to use the term fizz out for a min. Fizzing out for a minute: She clarified and states that the last two times this happened she did not fizz out, but she still just peed out of nowhere, without even having a sensation of having to pee. The last time she fizzed out was 10Apr2021. She doesn't know what to do and she is hoping that it gets figured out. She went four days without anything happening and then she was waiting in line and it just happened. She states she just urinated but doesn't recall fizzing out. She states it is not every day but every four days now, the urine. She states that it happened after the second vaccine. Dates for loosing urine was 04Mar2021. Physician Office visit for all events (went to the doctor after this happened. She states that the events might of happened before the second vaccine, she is not sure, but she started righting it down shortly after receiving the second vaccine). SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 74-year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE) via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Left on 18Mar2021 10:30 (Lot Number: ER2613) as 2ND DOSE, SINGLE for covid-19 immunisation. Medical history included supraventricular tachycardia from Dec2020 and ongoing; ongoing blood pressure high; she was diagnosed with high blood pressure post pregnancy. She said the last 6 weeks of her pregnancy she had toxemia. Her blood pressure was up, then went back down, and then shot back up. She experienced tachycardia at the time too. She took atenolol for 46 years for her high blood pressure. She was confident she had the COVID-19 Virus in Jan2020 before anyone knew about the pandemic. She and her husband got the COVID-19 vaccine so they could visit family, whose son was diagnosed with multiple myeloma. They were planning to go in Jun2021 for a visit, and her husband's family wouldn't let them visit unless both of them had the COVID-19 vaccine. No additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer suspect. No Prior Vaccinations within 4 weeks. Concomitant medications included in the morning of 18Mar2021 she took atenolol 25 mg tablet that was dispensed in a pharmacy. She regularly took atenolol 25 mg, twice a day. She also took olmesartan 5 mg (NDC Number: 16729-320-15, Lot Number: M2015864, Expiration Date: Oct2022). She regularly took olmesartan 5 mg, twice a day. She clarified 4 days after her second COVID-19 Vaccine, her cardiologist's Nurse Practitioner increased her olmesartan dose from 5 mg twice a day to olmesartan 10 mg, twice a day. The increased Olmesartan dosage gave her a monstrous headache. The cardiologist's nurse practitioner told her she would also need a blood test to make sure the olmesartan increased dose wasn't affecting her kidneys. Her primary care doctor asked how she was tolerating the increased olmesartan dose. She told her doctor she wasn't happy that the olmesartan could affect her kidneys and the headaches were killers. Her doctor told her that headaches were a side effect of olmesartan. She stayed on the increased olmesartan dosage for 3 weeks before her primary care doctor decreased her olmesartan dose back to 5 mg, twice a day on 17Apr2021. She said she had to go back to her doctor on 17May2021 for a follow-up appointment. She said her headaches were not as frequent since she reduced the olmesartan dose to 5 mg, twice a day. She still had headaches in the morning, and headaches at night, but was OK during the day. She treated her headaches with a cold cloth on her forehead. She said if her headache was extreme, she would take generic acetaminophen 500 mg caplet (100 caplets/bottle, NDC Number: 36800-484-78, Lot Number: GE2569C, Expiration Date: Apr2022) a couple times. She had to use a magnifying glass to read the Acetaminophen 500 mg caplet product label as the type was very tiny of the product label, and she was using reading glasses. She took regularly hydrochlorothiazide, triamterene (TRIAMTERENE/HCTZ, manufacturer Lannett) 37.5 mg/25 mg tablet, once a day. Primary care doctor kept her on regular visits to monitor her blood pressure. The patient previously received first dose of BNT162B2 (Lot Number: EN6205) Intramuscular in her left arm on 25Feb2021 had no reaction to the first COVID-19 Vaccine. She said within 30 minutes after getting the second COVID-19 Vaccine on 18Mar2021, her heart was racing. Her heart felt like it was fluttering in her chest. She said she felt very hot and was not comfortable. She said in the car, on the way home from getting her second COVID-19 Vaccine, her husband wanted to take her to the Emergency Room. She said she didn't feel it was critical, and her heart racing felt like the tachycardia she had experienced in the past. She said she called the COVID-19 Vaccination facility when she got home. She said she was told by them to lay down and rest for a while to see if that helped, and if she had chest pain or wasn't feeling better, to go to the Emergency Room. She said she went to bed, and laid down at their suggestion, and it took about 48 hours for her heart rate to settle down completely. She clarified when she first checked her heart rate, her heart rate was 116. She said prior to the COVID-19 Vaccine, her normal resting heart rate was 58, and now her resting heart rate is around 66. She said her blood pressure went out of control, too, and she had not been able to get her blood pressure under control since. She said she checked her blood pressure when she got home from her second COVID-19 Vaccine. She said her blood pressure would go up and then come down. She said the highest blood pressure reading she experienced (after getting her second COVID-19 Vaccine) was 201/116, and her lowest blood pressure reading (since then) was 152/96. She said her blood pressure at 11:00 PM last night (29Apr2021) was 168/93. She said prior to getting the COVID-19 Vaccine, her blood pressure averaged 139/83 with her lowest reading being 121/79. She said now her blood pressure readings average between 155-165/80s. She said her primary care doctor, and her cardiologist were in touch with each other about her medications. She said she breezed through her first COVID-19 Vaccine, but the second COVID-19 Vaccine had took a toll on her. She said from 2021 she had no energy and couldn't get out of her own way now. She said she was not the typical 75-year-old. She said she didn't retire until she was 70-year-old and was very active up until the time she received her second COVID-19 Vaccine. The events require a visit to physician office. She didn't take any over-the-counter or prescription medications for Heart Racing, but went to bed, laid down, and rested. She was very cautious about taking over-the-counter medications with her prescription medications. She said she tried to limit taking over-the-counter medications because she thought it was safer to do so. She checked her blood pressure when she got home from her second COVID-19 Vaccine. She said she had been tracking and checking her blood pressure, and took her blood pressure readings to her primary care doctor. She said her doctor made a copy of her blood pressure readings and put the blood pressure readings in her medical file. She said her blood pressure would go up and then come down. She said the highest blood pressure reading she experienced (after getting her second COVID-19 Vaccine) was 201/116, and her lowest blood pressure reading (since then) was 152/96. She said her blood pressure at 11:00 PM last night (29Apr2021) was 168/93. She said prior to getting the COVID-19 Vaccine, her blood pressure averaged 139/83 with her lowest reading being 121/79. She said now her blood pressure readings average between 155-165/80s. She didn't take any medication specifically to treat the high blood pressure after the second COVID-19 Vaccine. She had already took her regular medications that morning (18Mar2021) before she went for the COVID-19 Vaccine. The outcome of event her heart was racing, her heart felt like it was fluttering in her chest, felt very hot, she was not comfortable was recovered in Mar2021, of event she had not been able to get her blood pressure under control was not recovered, of events had no energy and tachycardia was unknown.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pericardial effusion tamponade; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 67-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine), dose 2 via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Right on 23Feb2021 (Batch/Lot Number: EN8208) at the age f 66 years old as 2nd dose, single for covid-19 immunisation. Medical history was not reported. The patient's concomitant medications were not reported. The patient previously received first dose of BNT162B2 on 31Jan2021, (Lot Number: EL9264) in the right arm at the age of 66 for COVID-19 vaccination. The patient reported that she began having signs and symptoms on 29Mar2021; heavy weight in throat like there was a softball in her throat; pressure in that area when she bent over; chest tightness; difficulty breathing; a lot of chest pain; chest stiffness; sharp stabbing pain in upper left chest. The patient stated that it took 13 days and 2 trips to the ER and multiple Doctor calls before they could diagnose what was wrong. She had visited her general doctor who thought she had an embolism and sent her to the Emergency Room on her second visit. They did a D-Dimer test, which they hadn't done on her first Emergency Room visit. The patient was diagnosed with pericardial effusion tamponade on 08Apr2021 as confirmed with the echocardiogram performed on 09Apr2021. On 09Apr2021 they removed the fluid, 700cc of blood, surrounding her heart. The patient was in the ICU from 08Apr2021 to 16Apr2021. The patient stated that she was hoping she would be able to transfer to a hospital but she was in too bad of shape to be transferred. The patient reported that she has some mild symptoms, residual symptoms, some pain in chest and some tightness, but it was much better now. She had an echocardiogram a week after getting out of the hospital which showed no fluid now. The patient was placed on medication. The outcome of the event was recovering.  Follow-up attempts are needed. No further information is expected.

She explained her PCP recommended her to get the second dose of the vaccine and said, it's better than nothing or [she] won't be immunized. She explained her cardiologist sent that message to her through an unspecified intermediary after she informed him of her side effects from the vaccine. She also mentioned she cannot take the Flu vaccine since she had a terrible experience the fourth year, she took it. She explained she took the flu vaccine for 4 consecutive years, the first year she was fine but the following year she reacted, and her reaction worsened after each year. She asked if she should take the second dose of the vaccine after experiencing side effects from the first dose.  She explained she is left alone to make that decision and needs guidance. She felt just kind of weird. She guesses a little bit later on is when left arm started to feel a little sore but wasn't anything bad like bad soreness; she could feel it but not like ouch. The day she called the Cardiologist she was feeling lousy and that is when the Cardiologist relayed the message that if it got worse to call back or go to the emergency room. Cardiologist initially told her to contact her primary care physician and she thought why she would call her primary care physician when it's a heart problem she experienced; but she did call the primary care physician. angioedema; hives; in lips tingling at times; itching; rash; This is a spontaneous report from a non-contactable other hcp. The second in JAN 2021, 10 days after she broke out in hives and had some angioedema, in lips tingling at times, no throat closures.  Eye angioedema was the first sign, around the eyes, that went away and was off and on. On day 10 she woke up with this and has had it ever since. angioedema of the lips on and off.  Since Jan 21 she's been headed to toe with hives they never go away, some days her legs are just covered. On 2021, the reporter sated that, 5 days after 2nd vaccine angioedema around both eyes and that was gone now, she's been to dermatologist, immunologist and primary care physician and they've tried, prednisone, IV Benadryl, Zyrtec, Allegra, also done oatmeal baths for itching, dermatologist wanted to put her on cyclosporine, she didn't want to go on it because it's a strong antibiotic. They also gave her pepcid.  Reporter asked to have anyone else had anything like this and why it is lasting so long. Reporter stated that everyone was saying, it's an immune response, and give it time and see if it goes away.  her daughter woke up in a huge snowstorm the first time she had the angioedema with Mouth, she went to the Emergency Room, they gave her IV Benadryl, kept her there for a little while, sent her home on prednisone pack, not tapered, just 5 days of high dose prednisone. They wanted her to go back on the Prednisone but on a tapered dose, but, she didn't' want to take it because she was afraid it would come back worse than ever.  It never got better, not even on the high dose prednisone. Other than put her on the prednisone, there wasn't really anything more. 4 Months later it hasn't settled down.  Reporter asked her daughter to come to where she lives and see Dermatologist, and he ordered a bunch of labs and got it back and it all looked fine. He wanted to start her on cyclosporine, she wanted to wait, didn't want to take it. Reporter stated, "It wipes the immune system out. They give it to transplant patients. they all say It's an immune response, it should settle down. Her daughter has been trying to change her diet, eating things low in histamines, cut out tomatoes, cut out cheeses, everything high in histamines, it doesn't make a difference.  Reporter stated, One day they are not quite so bad and then she wake's up and she was covered. Her daughter can't walk, or swim cause hot and cold makes her break out, or makes it worse, because it never goes away. Patient is a 14 YO male with no previous medical history that received the Pfizer vaccine administered into his left Deltoid at 1406. He was sent to the observation area where the nurse noted him looking pale at 1410. His mother was present during this whole event. He was taken over to the medical tent for privacy and further evaluation. He was complaining of being light headed. He was given apple juice and crackers as he had stated that he had not eaten or drank anything all day.    At 1430 his VS read BP 132/80, HR 145, O2 99%. At this time he was lying down and feet elevated, shaking, pale, and cold. Lung sounds clear. Nausea but not needing to throw up he was covered up to try and keep him warm. At 1440 his blood pressure was 130/82, HR 130, 02 98% At this time he was lying flat with feet elevated, shaking, pale, and cold. His lung sounds clear.  Nausea, but not needing to throw up.  At 1450 BP 138/74, HR 120-135, 02 98%. Symptoms had not changed at this point except he mentioned his ears felt cold, although they were warm to touch.  He was laid on his left side at this point to try and lower his HR, which did come down to 115-125 when on his L side. We did not take a BP at this point as we wanted him to be on his back when taking them.  At 1515 he was laid back on his back to see how his HR would do and how his BP was. BP 138/60, HR 135, 02 98%. Again symptoms were the same except he was complaining of colors being more ?dull?, and his teeth being numb. At this point his pupils were noted to be +8, equal and reactive.  1521 VS read 138/50, HR 135, 02 98%. Vision still dull and pupils unchanged from 1515. He was laid on his R side to see if this would lower his HR. It was brought down to 120-130 on his R side. We gave him a cookie to snack on to see if that would help with any of the paleness, shakiness, and light headiness. He was able to take a few small bites.  Hands pale and washed, with +1 bilateral radial pulses.  1529 he was sat up slowly to try to get him to hydrate, as it was apparent he needed fluids onboard. His BP read 142/80, HR 124, 02 98%. He was still complaining of lightheadedness. After sitting up and drinking half a bottle of water and some cookie, he stated that colors were becoming more vibrant. He noticed my eyes were very blue, which previously he had stated they were grey. He stated his lightheadedness had improved and that he was feeling better. We had him sit up for a while and his color started to come back, although his L arm was still pale, of note this was the Vaccinated arm.  At 1546 his VS read 150/82, HR 117, O2 99% while sitting. His only complaint was feeling like the air he was breathing ?was cold?.    At 1607 he was stood up and when doing so his HR went to 140. After standing for about 4 minutes his BP read 120/82, HR 114, O2 98%. His pupils +6 , equal, round, and reactive.  He was feeling way better and his color in his L hand was back equal to his right. He was slowly walked around a chair just to see how he would do with activity. His HR was anywhere from 94-120 when walking around the chair, he complained of no dizziness, or other symptoms.  At this point he had finished 2 apple juices, crackers, a cookie, and a bottle of water for a total of 1.5 L of fluid.  He was sat back down in the chair to rest and see how things went for a while. His HR was anywhere from 109-120 when in the chair, although he did appear very anxious through this whole process. When he was given a task it appeared that his HR was a few points lower.   His final HR was 109, BP 130/82, O2 98%.  Of note he did complain of his feet and fingers feeling tingly a few times during this process. Sometimes his feet would be tingly when elevated and then when the garbage can holding them up was readjusted it resolved. These were intermittent complaints.  At this point it is 1630. He has responded to fluids and is stable to go home with his mom. It was recommended for him to increase his fluids tonight, and to eat something. He was sent with a bottle of water. It was also recommended to get a pulse ox machine from a pharmacy so that his HR could be monitored and if it does not come down under 100 by tomorrow to make an appointment with his MD to follow up.  If any of these symptoms were to come back or if his mom had any concern at all it was recommended to take him to the ED for observation. It was also recommended to follow up with his primary even though he left stable.  Throughout this process, I considered administering Epinephrine. The problem was his BP was not low and we could not get his HR to come down. I did not want to increase his HR any more than it already was unless I was absolutely necessary. Given that he responded to fluids, it was decided not to administer it.   Given that it took him 2.5 hours to recover from this vaccine, I strongly recommend that he does not get his second dose. I consider this to be an adverse reaction, and his mom was in agreement.

Symptom Screening:  Initial reaction was noted on 1:30am (5/15). Mother states that pt's skin felt hot, +sweating, +chills. Mother did not physically take the temp. Mother gave him Aleve (2 tabs, unsure of dose) at 1:30am. And mother states that fever went away at 6am. Skin did not feel hot. Denies chills, sweating. Pt's mother noticed swelling lips at 7:30am in the AM (5/15).  Mother gave him 50mg of Benadryl at 9am.  Effect: "He seems very comfortable. Lips swelling is going down." Pt denies swelling tongue/eyes, hives, itchiness, wheezing, difficulty breathing, chest pain/ discomfort. Pt is breathing comfortably. Pt is eating and drinking fine. Mother stated, "He is joking around saying he does not need to do his lips." Denies any reaction to the injection site: Denies redness, itchiness, swelling.   Response/Recommendation   -Provided education to patients per guidelines as appropriate to the patient's clinical presentation.   -Provided home remedies.   -Educated the reasons to call the Nurse hotline, PCP office and the reasons go to the nearest ED if symptoms change or worsen.   -Continue to monitor for worsen lips swelling, tongue/ eyes swelling, wheezing, breathing difficulty, SOB, chest pain/discomfort, hives etc.  -If noticed any above symptoms and swelling lips does not go down completely with the Benadryl, go to the nearest ED or call 911.  -Informed to make sure to call in advance if seeking medical care so sites can be prepared to receive the case.  Good verbal return and agreed with the plan.    P.S: In the interim, since the lips swelling is going down, Pt's mother decided that she will wait and watch continuously and pt's mother is aware when to seek Emergency care.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Developed fatigue, arm soreness, and headache within a few hours of the shot. By nightfall, the headache had grown much worse. I developed a fever soon after waking that worsened to over 101 degrees by midday. My normal temperature is 97.2-97.6 so 101 is quite high for me. In short, I was miserable. I had covid for a month last February, but the side effects from the shot were worse, at least for me. This was like condensing the symptoms I had during the month I was sick with covid into a 24-hour period. Excruciating. By this morning (40 hours after shot), the worst of the side effects are over. I still have a mild, lingering headache, tiredness, and body aches, but I'm 90% better than I was this time yesterday.

This person sent an email to the Health Department relating the following:  She has a previous history of Bell's Palsy one year ago (March-April, 2020) which resolved.  She had new onset of Bell's Palsy on 4/2/21; 3 weeks after 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID19 vaccine dose.  She received her COVID19 vaccinations at Community Medical Center and she reported to me that she does not think anyone had submitted a VAERs on her behalf.  Patient states that her current episode of Bell's Palsy is NOT resolved and she is still having symptoms and treatment.  Details that she related to myself (via email) included that she has undergone 2 separate rounds of prednisone, facial rehab, and has an upcoming consultation with a neurologist scheduled in August.  I do not know the name of the physician she currently is under the care of for her Bell's Palsy.

According to my wife, 10 minutes post shot I had what appeared to be a mild seizure and lost consciousness for 1-2 minutes. Prior to that happening, I told her I felt light headed. She notified personnel while we were in the 15 min wait holding area and when I regained consciousness two EMTs were checking me out. They took my vitals, asked me questions and had me get out of the car and walk around. I was monitored for several minutes. It was recommended I visit a hospital or urgent care if I continued to feel unwell. My wife & I left the vaccine site and decided on the way home to go to the hospital just to ensure everything was all right. We went back home for about 30-60 minutes. During this time my heart rate continued to remain elevated and it felt like I had adrenaline coursing through my system. I attributed the feeling to recovering from passing out, but it did not dissipate.  Upon arrival to the ER I began having trouble trying to breathe and chest pain. During the triage EKG it was discovered I was experiencing atrial fibrillation. I was given treatment, fluids and monitored for several hours before being released. Estimated time from receiving shot to being diagnosed with afib was approximately 2.5-3 hours.
LAB_DATA: All tests/results happened 5/5/21 during ER visit; unsure exactly what everything is so I copied verbatim from the clinical discharge summary: - ECG / cardiovascular, - Consult / consult MD, - Cardiac monitor / patient care, - ED triage, chest pain CS / patient care, - IV insertion / patient care, - RN cont pulse oximeter / patient care, - Oxygen therapy / respiratory tx/proc, - Auto diff / general lab, - BMP / general lab, - CBC/diff / general lab, - CMP / general lab, - Est CrCl (CG) / general lab, - Pro BNP / general lab, - Rental funct index / general lab, - TSH / general lab - Trop T / general lab, - XR Chest 1V / radiology.

I felt fine after the shot, but two hours later, my throat felt like it was closing and it hurt in a way I've never felt before. I had a bad migraine and my whole body was sore. My blood pressure was high for me at 143/94 with a heart rate of 94. I trend at 120/80 with  a heart rate around 90. I take my blood pressure regularly to help manage Type II Diabetes.   I was concerned with my throat, as the other symptoms seemed normal for the vaccine. It was very uncomfortable. I phoned the nurse line and was told to have someone bring me to the ER to check me out and take a Benadryl. I took the Benadryl and packed for the ER with meds and ID and my friend drove me. I was still uncomfortable enough to warrant wanting to go and had become very dizzy.   When we got to the ER there was a wait and I went to my friend's car until called. After about 30 minutes (about 45 minutes after the Benadryl) my throat released and felt much better. My vitals were taken and seemed normal. The normal aches of the vaccine didn't concern me enough to stay, so I returned home.   My symptoms remain what seem to be normal reactions to the vaccine: sore joints, slight headache, slightly sore throat, Charlie horse feeling at the injection site. Nothing of major concern. My largest worry was with the throat feeling closed, but it appears the Benadryl took care of it.
OTHER_MEDS: Gemfibrozal 500mg 2x daily for triglycerides, Metformin 2x daily for Type II Diabetes

By day six, my swallowing had mostly returned to normal with a lingering "soft swallowing" feeling remaining.  I.E. it feels like the muscles performing the act of swallowing are weak.  As of today, 5/15/2021 (46 days after the 1 dose injection), I continue to experience times through out the day where the muscles for swallowing act weak.  It seems to slowly be returning to normal.  This is the first time that I have ever had something affect my throat or ability to swallow.  I have never had any adverse reactions to shots in the past nor do I have any allergies other than seasonal.

Received the Pfizer vaccine on April 13, 2021 (10 am) in the right arm.  Woke up the next day with a numb hand.  The numbness resolved temporarily, but a few days later experienced numbness and tingling in the entire arm as well as in the 4th and 5th fingers, along with a burning sensation in the right arm.  There was also some swelling and fullness in the hand, elbow, and upper arm.   Hand weakness and swelling in the lower forearm also occurred.  These symptoms persisted intermittently.  Went to see my doctor on April 26, 2021.  An Upper Extremity Ultrasound was performed to check for blood clots. The result was negative for Thrombus.  Advised to "wait and see" regarding the 2nd vaccine and to call if... ...other symptoms developed.   On May 1, 2021 had pain in left foot/ankle along with swelling.  Additionally, on May 4, 2021 pain and swelling developed in an area on the inside of the upper left leg.   Went to the doctor that morning (May 4th).  A Lower Extremity Ultrasound was performed to check for blood clots.  The result was negative for Thrombus.  Was advised to wait with the second vaccine for another week to see if symptoms would resolve.    As of May 15, 2021 symptoms continue, with intermittent swelling, numbness, and pain in the hand, elbow and arm.  Additionally, I have difficulty using my right hand due to continued weakness and numbness in the hand.   Since first seeing my doctor, I have been advised to take Motrin and/or Tylenol and apply heat and/or ice as needed for inflammation and pain.  Have been following this regimen for last few weeks with no significant improvement.  I have not received second vaccine, as symptoms still persist, and I have concerns that a similar or worse reaction may occur with the second dose.
LAB_DATA: April 26, 2021 - Ultrasound of Upper Extremity Veins (right) - Negative for Thrombus May 1, 2021 - Ultrasound of Lower Extremity Veins (left) - Negative for Thrombus

I, along with another  pharmacy customer,  a nurse, picked her up and placed her in a chair. She stated her blood sugar was low. The nurse asked that I take her blood pressure first. Patient asked that I go ahead and check her blood sugar. She stated that it had been up since she had a steroid shot 2 weeks ago. This had not been listed as a "yes" on her intake form. She had listed NO on this question. We grabbed a monitor off the shelf and tested it as well. Her blood pressure was checked 3 times and it would not register. The blood sugar registered 78. She stated that it normally ran 120 to 150. We gave her some water and was in the process of getting her some crackers and peanut butter. Within the first week after the vaccine, I began to get zapping electrical-like pains in the nerves in my fingertips and heels of my feet.  I developed sharp twitching of my limbs, fingers, and one night, even my tongue. A mild tremor that I had been feeling since a prior medication reaction (Tamoxifen) suddenly escalated.  Over the next week, the tremor began to have the same electrical quality in my upper arms and legs. It reminds me at times of that feeling when you chew on tinfoil. The shaking (whole body) wakes me at night and at times makes it impossible to drive, write, weave, or play my musical instrument. This week, I've had moments where my head literally wags like a dog's tail. My feet Charlie horse painfully. My upper arms and legs are developing a pervasive weakness, and I'm now unsteady on my feet. I'm sleeping more, napping many times in a day, and my usually boundless physical stamina is gone. Today I've had times of breathlessness. I can no longer function normally. If this continues, I will end up "disabled".
LAB_DATA: They've tested my thyroid, various mineral levels, and did bloodwork for myasthenia gravis. I had an exam with a neurologist and endocrinologist to see what could be the cause, and will have an MRI in the upcoming week. The condition is continuing to increase. It is hard to know if it could've been vaccine induced, but I am now suspicious because of the timing. Or maybe the vaccine kicked off something autoimmune.
OTHER_MEDS: Tamoxifen 20 mg Vitamin D 4000 units Magnesium powder
PRIOR_VAX: Tetanus, anaphylaxis, 2003, age 44
ALLERGIES: Various antibiotics and medications Allergic reaction to tetanus vaccine in 2003

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt who experienced the severe (albeit within the normal expected range of possible side effects per manufacturer and CDC guidelines) went with his wife to get their second in their two-dose series. By evening male recipient who had marked rxn began to "feel bad" with tiredness, arm pain, and fatigue with the onset of headache. By midnight the wife was screaming for me (the son) to come help. The pt was shivering so bad he couldn't walk. He was in severe pain along with his headache.  He experienced rapid onset nausea which despite oral tablet 12.5mg of Phenergan around 9:30 PM and was given 25 mg of liquid oral promethazine (20ml).  He held down the liquid promethazine for approx 15 minutes and violently threw it up.  During this time a large hot bath was drawn in the whirlpool tube which he stripped and entered. He was also made some hot tea with honey and given two glasses of that to help with internal GI warming.  A heating pad was placed in his bed under the sheets for when he exited to aid in the warming process. Once out of the bath, warmed, in warmer clothing - and having held down the tea he was given 8mg Zofran ODT which was well tolerated. Pt was observed from approx midnight to 6 AM when he got up and was able to perform his normal household morning "rituals" under his own mental faculties without assistance. **IN regards to question 21 below** the person making this report now - is a critical care paramedic, FF, instructor, and has a background in field and trauma medicine as well.  Outside of working 20 years on an ambulance/fire truck I also worked in the clinical medical setting with an extension of my license in family/internal medicine, rheumatology and immunology, and pediatrics. I had spent years giving vaccines, entering data into state systems after administration of vaccines, as well as using the VAERS systems when there were "adverse events." Diagnostics devices were here at the house for temperature, blood pressure, blood sugar, O2 saturation, etc.  There is a local hospital 1 mile away. I felt QUITE comfortable treating the patient at home with my skills - and if at any point I felt there had been a significant adverse si/sx emerge I would have ensured the pt went to a higher level of care.  Also how I am able to remember and provide certain details in this report. I have left the pt's name and the majority of his identifying information out BECAUSE "he doesn't trust government databases."
OTHER_MEDS: RX: Nuerontin 300mg TID, Singulair 10mg QD, Zyrtec-d PRN, Sudafed PRN, tylenol prn, advil prn, BC prn.  OTV vitamins: mens health 50+ gummies, fiber capsules, D3, Garlic, Vit-C, potassium
HISTORY: Some GI issues managed by weight and diet in consultation with regular scopes and GI doctor recommendations. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within approx. 5 minutes of receiving vaccine another patient (not related) alerted pharmacy staff to a patient "having a reaction" in our waiting area.  When I approached the patient, he was staring ahead at his mother while she informed me that he experiences similar reactions when at the doctors office when he receives any shot.  Before I approached he was passed out, but he was coming to when I arrived.  He was able to speak, look at me, and move without delay within a minute and showed no further symptoms.

About 10 minutes after the vaccine the patient complained of headache/lightheadedness.  We supplied the patient with a bottled water and he drank some. About 3 minutes later the patient complained of not feeling well/right.  His eyes then rolled back in his head and he began to shake. He did slump to the side in his wheelchair.   He was breathing although it seemed a bit labored. He was not responsive verbally when w asked him if he was ok. After about 2 minutes, the episode seemed to end.  He moved and  straightened up. His eyes opened and he was able to answer questions. He complained of feeling tired. He wanted to lay down and he said his stomach was a bit upset. 911 was called while the patient was not responding. They arrived after he awakened. He was given oxygen and eventually placed on a gurney and taken to the ER.
CUR_ILL: Patient  was living in Rehab unit due to a fall.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had been working all day in her flower gardens.  At 4:30 p.m. she felt like she had double vision and difficulty talking.  She does not remember much of what happened after that, but her husband said she had sudden onset of right arm weakness, leg weakness and drooping of the right side of her face.  Denies having numbness.  He immediately called 911 and EMS took her the Hospital.  She had a CT scan of the head that was negative.  When she arrived at the emergency room her symptoms had resolved, but she had recurrent episode of her symptoms in the emergency room with an NIH score of 5 scoring a point for level of consciousness, best language, and dysarthria and 2 points for facial droop.  She was given tPA and her symptoms resolved.  A CT angio of her head and neck did not show any large thrombus.  She was transferred for ongoing care and neurology evaluation.  Neuro deficits resolved.  Patient was discharged the second day after the event on Aspirin, Plavix and Lipitor.  Hospitalist (Dr) asked me to file VAERS report given recent Janssen vaccine administration.
LAB_DATA: CT of head 5/13: no acute findings, CT-angiogram: No evidence of intracranial large vessel occlusion.  MRI Brain 5/14: Left thalamus 2 subcentimeter small regions of recent ischemic infarct. No hemorrhagic transformation. No evidence of acute hemorrhage.  Significant periventricular and subcortical T2 weighted hyperintensities likely from chronic microvascular disease.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 46-year-old, female. Alert, oriented X4, clear speech, able to answer to questions. No known medical conditions. History of severe allergies to peanuts. Patient states she had no adverse reaction to first dose of Pfizer. At 10:53 am, the patient received her second dose of Pfizer (lot number EW0182, expires on 08/2021) on left deltoid. Patient walked with a steady, balanced gait to EMT observation area. At 11:20 am, patient notified EMT that she ?saw floaters? immediately after receiving her vaccine. She describes seeing black spots. Patient reports dull pain at injection site immediately following vaccination. EMT assisted patient to anti-gravity chair. Patient remained A&Ox4 and talking to EMT. Lead RN was notified of reaction. RN requested vitals Q5 minutes for 30 minutes. At 11:24 am: BP of 136/88, HR 74, SPO2 99% and respirations of 16/min. Patient's husband was notified and he sat with patient. At 11:29 am: 132/88, SPO2 96%, HR 70, RR 16. Patient no longer reporting seeing black spots. At 11:34 am: BP 132/84, SPO2 99%, HR 76, RR 16. At 11:41 am: BP 132/88, SPO2 99%, HR 74, RR 12. At 11:44 am: BP 134/86, SPO2 99%, HR 70, RR 16. Patient was A&Ox4 with no reports of dizziness and lightheadedness. Lead RN provided patient with education concerning when to call 9-1-1, including worsening of symptoms and trouble breathing. Patient was instructed to follow up with PCP. At 11:50 am, patient stood up from chair, denied lightheadedness and dizziness. Patient walked to car with steady, balanced gait. Patient's husband drove patient home.

10:25 AM. Patient was in Observation Area post vaccination 2nd dose of Pfizer.  Suddenly, she complained to RN who was the Observation Nurse that she has the pressure in her Left arm radiating to her neck and chest. She looked pale and clammy too. Oxygen saturation was on 83%, HR 93, Temp 97.5. No blood pressure taken due to unavailability of the apparatus at the site. 911 was called and took the patient into their VAn.
LAB_DATA: EKG and Blood sugar were taken by EMS.  Actual vitals and BG and EKG results were not reported by EMS due to Hippa protocol, but according to them, all Vitals weere within normal level. Patient was released by the EMS thereafter

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have never had any type of heart palpitation before.  I have also never had any heart trouble nor high blood pressure or anything of the sort.   The only sort of health condition I have is some varicose veins from prior pregnancies.     But about 3 days after the vaccine I was sitting on the floor and suddenly my heart started going crazy.  It was beating way faster than if i had suddenly over exerted.   I have never felt it beat so fast before.    I looked down and my whole chest was vibrating.   It felt like a lump was in my throat.  It was pretty scary.    I don:t know what the rate got up to.  It took me awhile to find something to measure it with and it had calmed down some by then but it still registered 140 bpm.  My rate is usually around 75bpm and I was doing nothing but just sitting on the floor when it happened.   It only lasted a few minutes, but my left arm ached a few more days and my heart seemed like it was beating stronger than normal for about 2 weeks (but when I checked it pulse rate and pressure were normal).   That was the only time it happened.  Otherwise i just had a sore arm and a headache for about 2 days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient informed me before giving the second dose of Moderna that she has fainted for every single vaccine she has ever been given including the first dose of Moderna. She stated it usually happens one to two minutes after receiving the vaccine and that she comes to within 10-15 minutes. Her father has been with her for every vaccination, and she just rests her head on his stomach. I informed the other pharmacist on duty of this and had EpiPen and smelling salts on hand just in case. We were all ready to react in case of any emergency. The patient did faint after sitting for a couple of minutes. She knew it was about to happen and her father stepped in to let her rest her head. We had her feet raised on a chair. She was still breathing the entire time, so we used smelling salts to bring her to which worked. She was out for close 10 minutes, but still breathing normally. The smelling salts enabled her to respond and nod that she was okay. When she came to, she asked for water and a sticker, which we gave her, and she acted as if nothing had happened and was all smiles. We did get a member of management to come fill out a report.
PRIOR_VAX: Patient states she has fainted for every vaccination she has ever been given.
